      <body>
         <head rend="center"><title type="main"><emph rend="italic">Epitaph</emph>.<emph
                  rend="super">1</emph><note type="head" place="bottom"><emph rend="super">1</emph>
                  Published in <emph rend="italic">The Balance and Columbian Repository</emph>
                  [Hudson, NY] (August 14, 1804).</note></title></head>
         
         <lg type="stanza">
            <l rend="indent">Here lies John Fish,</l>
            <l rend="indent">Who did earnestly wish</l>
            <l>The baits of Old Satan to shun:</l>
            <l rend="indent">And if that he shou'd</l>
            <l rend="indent" n="5">Be caught in the mud,</l>
            <l>To the net of salvation to run.</l>
            <l rend="indent">And when drawn by death's hook</l>
            <l rend="indent">From this turbulent brook,</l>
            <l>The scene of his sorrow and strife,</l>
            <l rend="indent" n="10">That he might not be cramm'd</l>
            <l rend="indent">On the coals with the damn'd,</l>
            <l>But swim in the waters of Life!</l>
         </lg>
